1
00:01:37,464 --> 00:01:38,031
Hello.

2
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:39,265
The phone you have dialed

3
00:01:39,365 --> 00:01:40,066
is powered off.

4
00:01:47,841 --> 00:01:48,274
Brother.

5
00:01:49,042 --> 00:01:49,442
Brother.

6
00:01:50,343 --> 00:01:50,910
Don't panic yet.

7
00:01:51,711 --> 00:01:52,645
The firefighters are already on site

8
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:53,146
conducting the rescue.

9
00:01:53,613 --> 00:01:54,347
And we can't be sure

10
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:55,415
he was definitely in the car.

11
00:01:55,415 --> 00:01:56,149
But his phone is still off.

12
00:01:56,149 --> 00:01:57,383
I can't find him.

13
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:10,029
Be careful.

14
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:11,197
High fall from the cross-sea bridge.

15
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:11,831
Cardiac tamponade.

16
00:02:11,998 --> 00:02:12,765
Suspected cardiac rupture.

17
00:02:13,032 --> 00:02:13,566
Be careful.

18
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:14,334
Slowly. Slowly.

19
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:15,435
There was another person.

20
00:02:15,869 --> 00:02:16,536
There was another person in the car.

21
00:02:16,569 --> 00:02:17,203
He was tall,

22
00:02:17,203 --> 00:02:18,104
about my age.

23
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:18,771
I don't know.

24
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:19,572
We only brought this one in.

25
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,212
He'll be fine.

26
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:27,647
He'll be fine.

27
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:29,182
Could he have been

28
00:02:29,182 --> 00:02:30,450
sent to another hospital?

29
00:02:31,918 --> 00:02:33,152
Or maybe he hasn't been...

30
00:02:34,287 --> 00:02:35,155
The cross-sea bridge, right?

31
00:02:36,022 --> 00:02:36,689
Let's go to the scene.

32
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:37,624
Let's go now.

33
00:02:37,790 --> 00:02:38,725
Okay. I'll drive.

34
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:39,559
The car keys are in the office.

35
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,267
Are you okay?

36
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:22,769
Are you hurt?

37
00:03:26,673 --> 00:03:27,574
Lin Yi.

38
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:31,811
Why was your phone off?

39
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,146
Why was your phone off?

40
00:03:33,313 --> 00:03:34,547
Why was your phone off?

41
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:35,915
I left my phone in his car.

42
00:03:35,915 --> 00:03:38,151
You always make me worry like this.

43
00:03:39,686 --> 00:03:41,521
I was scared to death.

44
00:03:41,521 --> 00:03:43,289
Why is it always like this?

45
00:03:55,535 --> 00:03:56,202
I'm sorry.

46
00:03:57,704 --> 00:03:58,671
I made you worry.

47
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,054
Where is Director Sheng?

48
00:04:16,122 --> 00:04:16,823
He was just sent in.

49
00:05:01,601 --> 00:05:02,368
Do you hike?

50
00:05:08,908 --> 00:05:10,310
I really like climbing Dongshan

51
00:05:10,443 --> 00:05:11,244
at dawn.

52
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:14,280
I walk and stop along the way for hours

53
00:05:15,848 --> 00:05:16,516
until I reach the summit.

54
00:05:20,119 --> 00:05:21,587
You can overlook all of Dongjiang.

55
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:24,957
The sun is about to rise

56
00:05:24,957 --> 00:05:25,558
from the horizon.

57
00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:29,228
That moment...

58
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:30,863
have you ever seen it?

59
00:05:35,935 --> 00:05:37,103
The sky is just about to brighten.

60
00:05:38,104 --> 00:05:39,405
Everything is full of life.

61
00:05:44,210 --> 00:05:44,844
Just a little.

62
00:05:49,215 --> 00:05:50,316
I was just that close

63
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:54,854
to seeing the sun.

64
00:06:08,434 --> 00:06:09,168
Once this car

65
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:10,703
gets on the highway

66
00:06:11,437 --> 00:06:12,405
and into the fast lane,

67
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,007
it can't get off anymore.

68
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:20,012
No matter what kind of car it is,

69
00:06:20,446 --> 00:06:21,848
the steering wheel is always in human hands.

70
00:06:22,648 --> 00:06:23,716
No matter what road you're on,

71
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:25,318
as long as you're willing to hit the brakes,

72
00:06:26,486 --> 00:06:27,487
the car will stop.

73
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:29,422
Sometimes I feel

74
00:06:29,789 --> 00:06:31,324
you are the idealized

75
00:06:31,591 --> 00:06:32,625
version of myself.

76
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,531
Single-minded,

77
00:06:39,532 --> 00:06:40,366
focused only on surgery.

78
00:06:42,535 --> 00:06:43,669
I really wanted to protect

79
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,071
that cleanliness and purity.

80
00:06:49,942 --> 00:06:51,444
This world is noisy and chaotic.

81
00:06:52,512 --> 00:06:53,880
To always remain yourself

82
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:55,515
is a blessing.

83
00:06:59,452 --> 00:07:00,853
Running away won't solve anything.

84
00:07:02,054 --> 00:07:03,322
Even if you can escape physically,

85
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:07,126
your conscience will never let you pass.

86
00:07:39,992 --> 00:07:40,426
Get out.

87
00:07:45,264 --> 00:07:45,631
Get out.

88
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,206
I still don't understand

89
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:29,108
why he made

90
00:08:29,108 --> 00:08:29,909
that choice.

91
00:08:31,944 --> 00:08:33,279
And in the end, he let me get out of the car.

92
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:41,554
How is he now?

93
00:08:46,158 --> 00:08:47,727
The heart surgery part went very smoothly.

94
00:08:49,528 --> 00:08:50,429
But he's badly injured.

95
00:08:51,731 --> 00:08:52,398
Next,

96
00:08:53,065 --> 00:08:54,667
we have to see what Neurosurgery and Orthopedics say.

97
00:09:02,808 --> 00:09:03,676
The entire Heart Center

98
00:09:03,809 --> 00:09:04,911
is in complete chaos right now.

99
00:09:05,444 --> 00:09:06,112
I'll go take a look first.

100
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,073
Stay with me for a while.

101
00:10:05,004 --> 00:10:05,705
I'll never again

102
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:06,872
make you worry about me.

103
00:10:34,533 --> 00:10:35,768
The investigation team just left.

104
00:10:36,736 --> 00:10:37,603
How is he?

105
00:10:38,971 --> 00:10:39,905
He still hasn't woken up.

106
00:10:41,073 --> 00:10:42,575
Neurosurgery came by just now.

107
00:10:43,509 --> 00:10:44,910
They said the craniocerebral injury is too severe.

108
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:46,746
It doesn't look optimistic.

109
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,430
I really didn't expect

110
00:11:05,631 --> 00:11:06,399
that the person who finally filed

111
00:11:06,432 --> 00:11:07,533
a real-name report against Director Sheng

112
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:08,768
was Xiao Cheng.

113
00:11:09,635 --> 00:11:10,369
Xiao Cheng?

114
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:12,104
Who is Xiao Cheng?

115
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:15,574
The person in Europe

116
00:11:15,641 --> 00:11:17,143
who gave me the overseas account.

117
00:11:20,813 --> 00:11:21,614
Thanks to all of you.

118
00:11:22,915 --> 00:11:23,516
Otherwise,

119
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,085
I would definitely have been taken in too this time.

120
00:11:31,557 --> 00:11:32,525
There hasn't been any further bleeding.

121
00:11:33,426 --> 00:11:34,693
Her condition has been fairly good these past few days.

122
00:11:35,394 --> 00:11:36,295
She has made it through another hurdle.

123
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:38,197
You Xiaoli,

124
00:11:38,564 --> 00:11:39,665
you are very strong.

125
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:41,834
Hold on for one more day if you can.

126
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:43,636
Hold on for one more minute if you can.

127
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:44,904
Keep fighting.

128
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:39,525
Why are you here?

129
00:12:50,336 --> 00:12:50,769
Dr. Guo.

130
00:12:51,303 --> 00:12:52,004
A donor has appeared.

131
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:52,638
Really?

132
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:53,372
Where?

133
00:12:53,906 --> 00:12:54,406
Xijiang.

134
00:12:54,673 --> 00:12:55,174
Really?

135
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:56,675
You Xiaoli is in critical condition.

136
00:12:56,809 --> 00:12:57,910
She is now first on the priority list.

137
00:12:58,144 --> 00:12:58,944
That's wonderful.

138
00:12:59,245 --> 00:13:00,146
But from Xijiang to Dongjiang,

139
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:01,480
it will take four or five hours at the fastest.

140
00:13:02,314 --> 00:13:03,315
That is already the safe upper limit

141
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:04,350
for the donor heart-lung

142
00:13:04,383 --> 00:13:05,117
cold ischemia time.

143
00:13:05,518 --> 00:13:06,085
I've already contacted

144
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:07,153
the green transport channel.

145
00:13:08,721 --> 00:13:09,321
If we really proceed,

146
00:13:09,488 --> 00:13:10,556
we also have to consider her bleeding

147
00:13:10,723 --> 00:13:11,423
and infection.

148
00:13:11,757 --> 00:13:12,191
We must request

149
00:13:12,224 --> 00:13:12,825
an MDT consultation.

150
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:13,893
I'll request it.

151
00:13:19,231 --> 00:13:19,765
Sorry.

152
00:13:19,765 --> 00:13:20,266
Excuse me, excuse me.

153
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,534
If we don't do

154
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:22,268
this surgery,

155
00:13:23,035 --> 00:13:24,203
the patient will certainly die.

156
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:25,971
I've already reviewed it.

157
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:27,006
The patient's infection

158
00:13:27,006 --> 00:13:28,641
has been effectively corrected.

159
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:29,408
I see she has been on

160
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,376
ECMO support

161
00:13:30,409 --> 00:13:31,310
for more than ten days,

162
00:13:31,677 --> 00:13:33,145
and her liver and kidney function are still acceptable.

163
00:13:33,812 --> 00:13:34,079
Yes.

164
00:13:34,547 --> 00:13:35,915
The patient is really fighting hard.

165
00:13:36,215 --> 00:13:37,283
From that perspective,

166
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:38,584
for postoperative recovery,

167
00:13:38,784 --> 00:13:39,752
there is at least a small

168
00:13:39,752 --> 00:13:40,452
positive factor.

169
00:13:41,387 --> 00:13:42,655
The patient can't hold on much longer.

170
00:13:43,956 --> 00:13:45,224
Even if there is only a glimmer of hope,

171
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:46,959
we should take the chance.

172
00:14:00,973 --> 00:14:01,307
Then take it.

173
00:14:23,596 --> 00:14:24,129
We're counting on you,

174
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:25,998
Director Zhou.

175
00:14:45,184 --> 00:14:45,684
Thank you for your hard work.

176
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,170
There is currently widespread

177
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:05,838
traffic congestion across the urban area.

178
00:15:06,272 --> 00:15:07,406
A small team will meet you at the highway exit

179
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:07,907
to receive you.

180
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,375
Okay. Understood.

181
00:15:26,292 --> 00:15:26,759
Thank you for your hard work.

182
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:28,127
Don't worry. No problem.

183
00:15:42,574 --> 00:15:44,143
Between an indifferent heaven and earth,

184
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:46,345
life is fragile.

185
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:49,615
But countless tiny ants

186
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:50,616
gather together.

187
00:15:51,183 --> 00:15:52,718
With unyielding will,

188
00:15:53,252 --> 00:15:55,487
they work together to protect their companions.

189
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:59,825
And because of that,

190
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,493
the whole colony continues to thrive.

191
00:16:06,598 --> 00:16:08,167
Xiaoxiao and her friends

192
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,168
were very worried.

193
00:16:09,768 --> 00:16:11,203
For ants so weak,

194
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:13,272
apart from attacks from natural enemies,

195
00:16:13,772 --> 00:16:15,307
the wind could blow them away,

196
00:16:15,908 --> 00:16:17,609
the rain could wash them away,

197
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:20,279
and pedestrians' steps could crush them.

198
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:22,848
But the ants told Xiaoxiao

199
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:25,951
that ants can

200
00:16:26,051 --> 00:16:27,252
use tight formations

201
00:16:27,886 --> 00:16:29,488
to quickly gather together.

202
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:31,590
They divide their work clearly

203
00:16:32,091 --> 00:16:33,192
and fight bravely.

204
00:16:48,474 --> 00:16:48,907
Thank you for your hard work.

205
00:18:47,092 --> 00:18:47,593
You Xiaoli.

206
00:18:50,729 --> 00:18:51,330
You Xiaoli.

207
00:18:52,197 --> 00:18:52,831
You're awake.

208
00:19:06,745 --> 00:19:07,479
Doudou seems

209
00:19:07,679 --> 00:19:09,014
to have grown noticeably.

210
00:19:10,282 --> 00:19:10,682
Yes.

211
00:19:10,883 --> 00:19:12,184
His little heart

212
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:13,752
is gradually regaining strength.

213
00:19:13,886 --> 00:19:15,454
His heart rate has also steadily decreased.

214
00:19:15,754 --> 00:19:17,256
The respiratory support settings

215
00:19:17,356 --> 00:19:18,357
are also being steadily lowered.

216
00:19:18,590 --> 00:19:19,158
His gastrointestinal function

217
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,159
has begun to improve too.

218
00:19:20,425 --> 00:19:21,126
That means

219
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:22,161
the most dangerous stage

220
00:19:22,227 --> 00:19:22,961
has already passed.

221
00:19:23,228 --> 00:19:23,896
His condition

222
00:19:24,129 --> 00:19:25,130
is still very optimistic.

223
00:19:26,765 --> 00:19:27,566
Thank you, doctor.

224
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:28,267
You've worked hard.

225
00:19:28,634 --> 00:19:29,034
It's okay.

226
00:19:32,971 --> 00:19:33,839
Grow up quickly,

227
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:34,706
my little Doudou.

228
00:19:35,574 --> 00:19:37,042
Mom and Dad are still waiting for you.

229
00:19:40,879 --> 00:19:41,313
Dr. Fang.

230
00:19:58,564 --> 00:19:58,830
Hello?

231
00:19:59,364 --> 00:19:59,765
Brother.

232
00:20:00,132 --> 00:20:01,133
Our cardiomyopathy project

233
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:02,234
passed the review.

234
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:03,669
I just received the notice.

235
00:20:04,202 --> 00:20:04,770
Really?

236
00:20:05,203 --> 00:20:05,804
That's great.

237
00:20:06,438 --> 00:20:07,773
Send a screenshot of the notice to the group.

238
00:20:07,973 --> 00:20:08,874
Let everyone be happy too.

239
00:20:09,174 --> 00:20:10,042
Okay. I'll send it now.

240
00:20:10,509 --> 00:20:11,510
Let's also tell Professor Wu

241
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:12,344
this news.

242
00:20:21,286 --> 00:20:22,387
The investigation at MyAmpere

243
00:20:22,454 --> 00:20:23,322
has finally ended.

244
00:20:23,722 --> 00:20:24,823
I have progress on my side too.

245
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:27,693
You got the job offer?

246
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:29,528
It's a new type

247
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:30,362
of industrial company.

248
00:20:30,495 --> 00:20:31,563
Medicine-engineering integration.

249
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:32,931
They encourage doctors

250
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:34,766
to draw on their clinical experience

251
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,168
to do device innovation.

252
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:38,570
The manufacturer provides resources

253
00:20:38,704 --> 00:20:39,304
for experiments,

254
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:40,973
and finally turns the product into production.

255
00:20:41,473 --> 00:20:42,407
Impressive.

256
00:20:42,674 --> 00:20:43,742
You have a medical background,

257
00:20:44,042 --> 00:20:45,243
you understand medical devices,

258
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:46,278
and you know market demand.

259
00:20:46,545 --> 00:20:47,145
They need exactly

260
00:20:47,145 --> 00:20:48,013
talent like you.

261
00:20:48,313 --> 00:20:48,847
Exactly.

262
00:20:49,848 --> 00:20:51,283
That's why the salary is very high.

263
00:20:53,719 --> 00:20:54,987
Congratulations, Consultant Ouyang.

264
00:20:55,787 --> 00:20:56,688
Same to you.

265
00:20:57,489 --> 00:20:57,789
Come on.

266
00:20:58,323 --> 00:20:59,524
Cheers.

267
00:21:03,695 --> 00:21:04,730
Hello, Director Lin.

268
00:21:09,568 --> 00:21:09,935
Let's go.

269
00:21:11,503 --> 00:21:13,271
Haven't seen this scene in a long time.

270
00:21:13,572 --> 00:21:14,906
Where are those three going after work together?

271
00:21:15,274 --> 00:21:16,408
Where they're going doesn't matter.

272
00:21:16,642 --> 00:21:17,209
What matters is

273
00:21:17,342 --> 00:21:18,677
those three are leaving work together again.

274
00:21:20,078 --> 00:21:20,812
Did you see that?

275
00:21:20,912 --> 00:21:21,813
Director Lin is carrying the bag.

276
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:23,482
Good thing Director Lin doesn't have a tail.

277
00:21:23,548 --> 00:21:24,349
Otherwise it would've wagged off by now.

278
00:21:25,317 --> 00:21:26,385
Why are you so disrespectful?

279
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:38,363
Director Zhou.

280
00:21:38,730 --> 00:21:39,197
Director Lin.

281
00:21:39,331 --> 00:21:39,831
Dr. Fang.

282
00:21:40,399 --> 00:21:41,033
Liang Mei.

283
00:21:44,069 --> 00:21:44,636
Is everyone well?

284
00:21:44,836 --> 00:21:45,804
Yes, yes. All good.

285
00:21:46,071 --> 00:21:46,838
Not bad, Dadong.

286
00:21:46,872 --> 00:21:47,472
Full of energy.

287
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:48,373
Director Zhou.

288
00:21:49,241 --> 00:21:49,641
You're here.

289
00:21:50,876 --> 00:21:51,943
Is it far from school?

290
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:53,011
It's fine.

291
00:21:53,278 --> 00:21:54,079
There's a direct bus.

292
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:54,913
It only takes forty minutes.

293
00:21:55,614 --> 00:21:56,281
Then let's go.

294
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:51,703
I don't know who you are,

295
00:22:52,471 --> 00:22:53,372
but I have to thank you.

296
00:22:56,608 --> 00:22:57,042
Don't worry.

297
00:22:57,909 --> 00:22:58,477
I promise

298
00:22:58,543 --> 00:22:59,811
I'll take good care of this heart.

299
00:23:03,482 --> 00:23:04,449
Let's live on together.

300
00:23:08,854 --> 00:23:09,554
I know

301
00:23:10,389 --> 00:23:12,124
your name isn't carved here.

302
00:23:13,425 --> 00:23:14,326
But I believe

303
00:23:15,026 --> 00:23:16,628
you must have gone with them

304
00:23:17,796 --> 00:23:18,396
to a

305
00:23:18,430 --> 00:23:19,798
very happy place.

306
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:23,135
Thank you for helping me keep my mom.

307
00:23:24,903 --> 00:23:25,904
When Mom gets better,

308
00:23:27,706 --> 00:23:29,174
we'll go to Xijiang together to see you.

309
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:56,368
Director, you wanted to see me?

310
00:23:56,735 --> 00:23:57,302
Close the door.

311
00:24:20,492 --> 00:24:21,693
This is a letter from the family

312
00:24:21,693 --> 00:24:22,527
of the patient in Bed 15.

313
00:24:26,431 --> 00:24:27,866
Ma Qiran in Bed 15?

314
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:30,268
I went to see him today.

315
00:24:30,335 --> 00:24:31,169
He looked quite well.

316
00:24:31,803 --> 00:24:32,804
As soon as I walked in, his family

317
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:33,905
kept offering me fruit.

318
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:36,241
I didn't have any conflict with them.

319
00:24:41,213 --> 00:24:42,247
Copy it ten times before you leave.

320
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,638
Dear Dr. Ye Sisi,

321
00:25:07,105 --> 00:25:07,639
Hello.

322
00:25:08,306 --> 00:25:09,608
As I write this letter,

323
00:25:09,975 --> 00:25:12,043
my heart is filled with gratitude and admiration.

324
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,588
I came for treatment earlier

325
00:25:23,588 --> 00:25:24,289
because I felt unwell.

326
00:25:24,656 --> 00:25:25,490
When I first met you,

327
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:27,526
I was surprised by how young you were.

328
00:25:28,226 --> 00:25:28,994
But I didn't expect

329
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:30,395
that although you are so young,

330
00:25:30,795 --> 00:25:32,364
you possess professional competence

331
00:25:32,430 --> 00:25:33,231
and clinical experience

332
00:25:33,331 --> 00:25:34,266
far beyond your peers.

333
00:25:35,734 --> 00:25:37,068
From detailed consultation

334
00:25:37,302 --> 00:25:38,503
to precise diagnosis,

335
00:25:39,304 --> 00:25:40,772
at every step,

336
00:25:40,772 --> 00:25:42,440
you were patient and rigorous,

337
00:25:43,174 --> 00:25:44,843
which made me feel deeply reassured

338
00:25:45,143 --> 00:25:46,278
during the visit.

339
00:25:47,812 --> 00:25:49,514
Now my physical condition

340
00:25:49,648 --> 00:25:50,749
is improving

341
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:52,784
day by day.

342
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:55,720
This is inseparable from your precise treatment

343
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:57,589
and careful instructions.

344
00:25:59,157 --> 00:25:59,991
I sincerely wish you

345
00:26:00,091 --> 00:26:01,159
further achievements

346
00:26:01,593 --> 00:26:02,527
in your medical career

347
00:26:03,028 --> 00:26:04,162
and a bright future.

348
00:26:10,635 --> 00:26:12,370
Do I have to copy a thank-you letter too?

349
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:27,986
Suction.

350
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:33,158
Watch the position.

351
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:36,394
Not bad, Xiao Du.

352
00:26:36,628 --> 00:26:37,295
You're teaching others now.

353
00:26:40,999 --> 00:26:41,566
What are you looking at?

354
00:26:43,835 --> 00:26:44,569
Looking at Du Wenzheng.

355
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:46,571
He's already the first assistant,

356
00:26:46,571 --> 00:26:48,039
yet he's still clumsy and slow.

357
00:26:49,774 --> 00:26:50,108
Brother,

358
00:26:50,642 --> 00:26:51,509
you're a genius.

359
00:26:51,876 --> 00:26:52,911
You can't use a genius's standards

360
00:26:53,011 --> 00:26:54,045
to judge everyone.

361
00:26:54,245 --> 00:26:55,513
Especially your beloved student.

362
00:26:55,714 --> 00:26:56,214
Don't talk nonsense.

363
00:26:56,214 --> 00:26:56,948
He's not my student.

364
00:26:57,415 --> 00:26:58,783
He said you're his idol.

365
00:26:59,050 --> 00:27:00,085
Come on, forgive him. Forgive him.

366
00:27:00,185 --> 00:27:00,752
Let's get coffee.

367
00:27:00,885 --> 00:27:01,653
My treat. Let's go.

368
00:27:02,887 --> 00:27:03,888
Where are you going?

369
00:27:06,524 --> 00:27:07,826
Come on, let him do it.

370
00:27:08,593 --> 00:27:08,960
Director.

371
00:27:09,928 --> 00:27:10,795
Don't mind me. Do your work.

372
00:27:11,529 --> 00:27:12,130
I'm just watching.

373
00:27:21,606 --> 00:27:22,674
The little guy is fighting hard.

374
00:27:23,008 --> 00:27:24,476
Look at his tiny arms and legs.

375
00:27:24,542 --> 00:27:26,211
He's clearly put on some flesh.

376
00:27:26,911 --> 00:27:27,746
As the old saying goes,

377
00:27:28,346 --> 00:27:29,214
if the seedling is there, it will grow.

378
00:27:29,914 --> 00:27:30,215
Yes.

379
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:31,316
Little Doudou has sprouted.

380
00:27:32,350 --> 00:27:33,151
Hexuemei and her son

381
00:27:33,151 --> 00:27:33,985
are both doing well too.

382
00:27:34,285 --> 00:27:35,186
A few days ago, she sent some

383
00:27:35,186 --> 00:27:35,987
local specialties from Guizhou

384
00:27:36,187 --> 00:27:37,188
and told me I must give them to you.

385
00:27:37,956 --> 00:27:39,190
Her son and little Doudou

386
00:27:39,424 --> 00:27:40,091
can play together

387
00:27:40,091 --> 00:27:40,725
when they grow up.

388
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:42,527
Mom.

389
00:27:43,094 --> 00:27:44,329
How did you get here so fast?

390
00:27:45,997 --> 00:27:48,133
Xinjiang in winter is truly beautiful.

391
00:27:48,466 --> 00:27:49,167
At that time,

392
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:51,269
we had just left Sayram Lake

393
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:53,071
and were heading toward Hemu.

394
00:27:53,605 --> 00:27:54,706
Halfway there, I received

395
00:27:54,773 --> 00:27:56,641
a call from President Liang of Huachen.

396
00:27:57,409 --> 00:27:58,843
He asked me to fly to Chengdu for a surgery.

397
00:27:59,811 --> 00:28:00,211
When I calculated it,

398
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:03,815
it happened to be the day my medical license was restored.

399
00:28:04,582 --> 00:28:06,351
They had timed it perfectly.

400
00:28:06,718 --> 00:28:08,319
So I turned around and went to Chengdu.

401
00:28:08,319 --> 00:28:09,688
Once I got there, I couldn't leave.

402
00:28:10,388 --> 00:28:10,822
Then

403
00:28:11,089 --> 00:28:12,123
you left Shi Wei alone

404
00:28:12,157 --> 00:28:12,624
in Xinjiang?

405
00:28:14,559 --> 00:28:16,594
You know he understands me best.

406
00:28:17,162 --> 00:28:18,229
He knows I love work.

407
00:28:18,863 --> 00:28:19,564
So,

408
00:28:20,031 --> 00:28:21,466
we siblings both inherited

409
00:28:21,466 --> 00:28:22,734
your restless blood.

410
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:24,069
Right, brother?

411
00:28:25,403 --> 00:28:26,204
You're one to talk.

412
00:28:26,204 --> 00:28:26,771
You're now

413
00:28:26,805 --> 00:28:28,206
the one who can't sit still the most.

414
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:30,108
Your ICU work

415
00:28:30,175 --> 00:28:31,042
is already so busy.

416
00:28:31,176 --> 00:28:31,509
And you're also

417
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:34,145
running the cardiomyopathy research group.

418
00:28:34,946 --> 00:28:35,713
What about you?

419
00:28:36,147 --> 00:28:37,015
You're so busy too,

420
00:28:37,315 --> 00:28:39,050
yet you're quietly doing big things.

421
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:42,087
I want to establish

422
00:28:42,087 --> 00:28:43,088
a congenital heart disease volunteer clinic team.

423
00:28:43,955 --> 00:28:44,789
Starting from Dongli,

424
00:28:45,323 --> 00:28:46,391
we'll work with charities

425
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:47,492
to provide free congenital heart disease screening

426
00:28:47,525 --> 00:28:48,893
and treatment

427
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:50,695
for children in underdeveloped areas nationwide.

428
00:28:50,695 --> 00:28:51,229
That's wonderful.

429
00:28:52,063 --> 00:28:52,630
Both my children

430
00:28:53,064 --> 00:28:54,065
work so hard.

431
00:28:54,833 --> 00:28:55,633
As their mother, I can't fall behind.

432
00:28:56,434 --> 00:28:58,636
From the sound of that,

433
00:28:59,804 --> 00:29:00,805
do you have some new plan?

434
00:29:01,272 --> 00:29:02,841
This time,

435
00:29:03,374 --> 00:29:04,309
I met many old classmates.

436
00:29:04,309 --> 00:29:05,844
Like me,

437
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:06,478
they are retired but can't stay idle.

438
00:29:06,544 --> 00:29:07,879
So,

439
00:29:08,713 --> 00:29:09,347
we decided to form

440
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:11,549
an expert group called Never Look Back.

441
00:29:12,050 --> 00:29:13,451
Never Look Back Expert Group?

442
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:15,487
I've been a doctor all my life.

443
00:29:16,521 --> 00:29:18,089
I just feel

444
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:20,525
that only when I'm practicing medicine

445
00:29:20,825 --> 00:29:22,127
do I feel fulfilled.

446
00:29:22,127 --> 00:29:23,027
That state in the operating room,

447
00:29:24,829 --> 00:29:26,397
tense and excited,

448
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:28,867
that surge

449
00:29:30,235 --> 00:29:30,769
of endorphins and dopamine,

450
00:29:31,269 --> 00:29:33,705
cannot be replaced by anything else.

451
00:29:34,005 --> 00:29:35,673
And you feel

452
00:29:36,474 --> 00:29:37,442
that in this world,

453
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:38,676
some lives

454
00:29:39,511 --> 00:29:40,512
exist

455
00:29:41,646 --> 00:29:42,614
because of you.

456
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:44,149
Then what plans

457
00:29:50,655 --> 00:29:52,157
does your expert group have next?

458
00:29:52,690 --> 00:29:54,292
Work with hospitals around the country.

459
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:57,028
Fly-in surgery, consultations, training the next generation.

460
00:29:58,263 --> 00:30:00,231
The congenital heart volunteer clinic team

461
00:30:01,933 --> 00:30:02,867
requests cooperation.

462
00:30:03,201 --> 00:30:04,002
The cardiomyopathy research group

463
00:30:05,670 --> 00:30:07,105
asks to cut in line for guidance.

464
00:30:07,372 --> 00:30:08,406
Actually, I know

465
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:13,545
that during this period,

466
00:30:13,711 --> 00:30:14,646
in work and life,

467
00:30:14,712 --> 00:30:16,114
you both encountered

468
00:30:16,247 --> 00:30:18,316
quite a few difficulties.

469
00:30:18,950 --> 00:30:20,351
But you got through them.

470
00:30:21,186 --> 00:30:21,920
And you did

471
00:30:22,187 --> 00:30:23,188
even better than I imagined.

472
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:24,189
I'm proud of you.

473
00:30:25,623 --> 00:30:26,357
And I'm proud of you too.

474
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:28,560
Of course.

475
00:30:28,826 --> 00:30:29,427
The Bamboo Siblings

476
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:30,595
will never disappoint you.

477
00:30:31,196 --> 00:30:31,930
Bamboo Siblings?

478
00:30:32,030 --> 00:30:33,431
Why does that sound weird?

479
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:35,667
Ouyang is picking up Senlin,

480
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:36,534
so they'll still be a while.

481
00:30:37,168 --> 00:30:38,636
I'll check where Lin Yi is.

482
00:30:40,405 --> 00:30:41,773
He says he's already at the restaurant.

483
00:30:42,173 --> 00:30:42,640
Shall we go?

484
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:44,609
Let him wait a bit.

485
00:30:47,111 --> 00:30:47,445
Okay.

486
00:30:47,478 --> 00:30:47,712
Okay.

487
00:30:48,213 --> 00:30:48,880
Let him wait a bit.

488
00:30:49,047 --> 00:30:49,681
You wait a bit.

489
00:30:51,082 --> 00:30:52,150
Let's see who swings higher.

490
00:31:16,407 --> 00:31:17,875
The stent we placed for your husband

491
00:31:18,042 --> 00:31:19,544
is, after all, a metal support.

492
00:31:19,811 --> 00:31:20,745
So medication is needed

493
00:31:21,112 --> 00:31:21,913
to allow the vascular intima

494
00:31:21,946 --> 00:31:22,847
to smoothly cover it.

495
00:31:22,947 --> 00:31:23,514
After discharge,

496
00:31:27,285 --> 00:31:28,052
After discharge,

497
00:31:28,152 --> 00:31:29,554
you must pay special attention to the medication.

498
00:31:29,954 --> 00:31:30,388
If you notice

499
00:31:30,488 --> 00:31:31,589
any signs of bleeding,

500
00:31:31,689 --> 00:31:33,324
for example, unexplained gum bleeding,

501
00:31:33,358 --> 00:31:34,125
or bruising

502
00:31:34,192 --> 00:31:35,093
on the skin,

503
00:31:35,226 --> 00:31:36,427
you must come back promptly for follow-up.

504
00:31:37,161 --> 00:31:37,695
Okay, okay.

505
00:31:38,196 --> 00:31:38,963
Thank you, Director Zhou.

506
00:31:39,063 --> 00:31:40,064
If anything happens,

507
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:41,633
I'll come to the hospital to find you right away.

508
00:31:42,267 --> 00:31:42,800
Take care this way.

509
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:44,769
Take care.

510
00:31:47,038 --> 00:31:47,438
Director.

511
00:31:48,072 --> 00:31:48,673
Come look at this.

512
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:51,242
Quick, quick, quick.

513
00:31:52,143 --> 00:31:52,610
What is it?

514
00:31:53,511 --> 00:31:54,045
Look at this.

515
00:31:56,648 --> 00:31:57,415
Dilated cardiomyopathy.

516
00:31:57,415 --> 00:31:58,750
Penetrance in genotype-positive relatives.

517
00:32:03,721 --> 00:32:04,522
So according to

518
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:05,723
this latest statistical data,

519
00:32:06,024 --> 00:32:06,924
the mutant gene carried

520
00:32:06,924 --> 00:32:08,026
in Lin Yi's family,

521
00:32:08,126 --> 00:32:09,394
from a genetic perspective,

522
00:32:09,961 --> 00:32:11,062
has very low penetrance.

523
00:32:11,329 --> 00:32:11,696
Yes.

524
00:32:12,563 --> 00:32:13,598
And more importantly,

525
00:32:14,032 --> 00:32:14,832
the statistics show

526
00:32:15,166 --> 00:32:16,134
that this mutant gene

527
00:32:16,401 --> 00:32:16,868
generally causes disease

528
00:32:16,968 --> 00:32:17,835
when people are young.

529
00:32:18,069 --> 00:32:19,437
The earlier the onset, the worse the prognosis.

530
00:32:19,704 --> 00:32:20,305
The older the person,

531
00:32:20,405 --> 00:32:21,439
the lower the chance of onset.

532
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:23,641
Lin Yi is already thirty-nine.

533
00:32:24,108 --> 00:32:25,343
His heart is still very healthy.

534
00:32:27,345 --> 00:32:28,046
In other words,

535
00:32:29,347 --> 00:32:29,881
he is very likely

536
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:30,715
to escape this.

537
00:32:31,449 --> 00:32:32,116
Very likely.

538
00:32:33,751 --> 00:32:34,752
I guess from his mother's side,

539
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:36,554
there is a very strong modifier gene

540
00:32:37,188 --> 00:32:38,589
that compensated for his genetic deletion.

541
00:32:41,092 --> 00:32:41,492
Lin Yi

542
00:32:42,327 --> 00:32:43,194
probably

543
00:32:44,696 --> 00:32:45,830
will never develop the disease in this life.

544
00:33:01,846 --> 00:33:03,214
Why are you laughing? So happy.

545
00:33:04,415 --> 00:33:05,850
Can't I be happy just seeing you?

546
00:33:06,584 --> 00:33:07,151
Really?

547
00:33:07,185 --> 00:33:08,086
Seeing me makes you happy?

548
00:33:10,054 --> 00:33:11,155
So, what should we eat later?

549
00:33:11,356 --> 00:33:12,590
Seafood casserole, fish ball casserole,

550
00:33:12,623 --> 00:33:13,591
or a casserole you invent yourself?

551
00:33:13,725 --> 00:33:14,425
I've prepared all the ingredients.

552
00:33:14,592 --> 00:33:15,560
Stop thinking only about food.

553
00:33:15,626 --> 00:33:16,294
I want to go out and play.

554
00:33:16,761 --> 00:33:17,295
Where do you want to play?

555
00:33:17,762 --> 00:33:18,529
To the amusement park.

556
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:19,831
I want to play ring toss,

557
00:33:20,264 --> 00:33:20,832
throw sandbags.

558
00:33:21,399 --> 00:33:22,233
What's so fun about that?

559
00:33:23,201 --> 00:33:24,502
If you hit the target, you win a doll.

560
00:33:26,838 --> 00:33:27,705
You like dolls?

561
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:54,399
But the most important thing

562
00:33:55,833 --> 00:33:56,934
is a doctor's character.

563
00:34:04,442 --> 00:34:05,176
What are we eating later?

564
00:34:06,411 --> 00:34:06,944
Goodbye, Teacher Fang.

565
00:34:07,211 --> 00:34:07,545
Bye-bye.

566
00:34:07,545 --> 00:34:08,079
I'm so hungry.

567
00:34:08,746 --> 00:34:09,347
Goodbye, teacher.

568
00:34:09,347 --> 00:34:09,914
Bye-bye.

569
00:34:46,951 --> 00:34:47,718
What are you doing?

570
00:34:51,355 --> 00:34:52,490
Didn't you want to go to the amusement park?

571
00:34:53,357 --> 00:34:53,891
Let's play games.

572
00:34:56,694 --> 00:34:57,495
Let's play sandbag toss.

573
00:34:58,396 --> 00:34:59,030
Throw it at me.

574
00:34:59,397 --> 00:35:00,164
Hit the target and win a prize.

575
00:35:00,465 --> 00:35:01,332
Just this one ring?

576
00:35:08,239 --> 00:35:09,841
Life: yes or no.

577
00:35:10,775 --> 00:35:11,242
Start.

578
00:35:12,310 --> 00:35:13,211
How many chances do I get?

579
00:35:19,584 --> 00:35:20,284
Three chances.

580
00:35:21,719 --> 00:35:22,153
Start.

581
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:33,164
Xiaoran.

582
00:35:44,775 --> 00:35:45,243
Replay.

583
00:35:45,743 --> 00:35:46,878
Replay. That doesn't count.

584
00:35:47,512 --> 00:35:48,312
Come on, come on.

585
00:35:48,446 --> 00:35:48,846
Xiaoran.

586
00:35:49,914 --> 00:35:51,082
No matter what choice you make,

587
00:35:51,415 --> 00:35:52,984
I'll accept it willingly.

588
00:35:54,185 --> 00:35:55,386
Aim here. Here.

589
00:35:58,456 --> 00:35:59,824
Throwing at the small one

590
00:35:59,891 --> 00:36:00,591
is the only way to prove my skill.

591
00:36:00,591 --> 00:36:01,392
Stop messing around, Fang Xiaoran.

592
00:36:01,492 --> 00:36:02,293
You can't throw it here.

593
00:36:05,396 --> 00:36:06,731
You almost hit it.

594
00:36:06,731 --> 00:36:07,465
Throw it here.

595
00:36:07,765 --> 00:36:09,133
You have one last chance.

596
00:36:22,647 --> 00:36:23,281
Fang Xiaoran.

597
00:36:33,591 --> 00:36:34,158
Marry him.

598
00:36:34,292 --> 00:36:50,374
Marry him! Marry him! Marry him!

599
00:36:50,408 --> 00:36:50,908
Xiaoran.

600
00:36:51,242 --> 00:36:52,009
Marry him.

601
00:36:52,009 --> 00:36:52,810
Stop, stop, stop.

602
00:36:52,944 --> 00:36:53,511
Marry him.

603
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:25,476
Xiaoran.

604
00:37:27,478 --> 00:37:28,312
Fang Xiaoran.

605
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:31,115
Dr. Fang.

606
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:34,485
Director Lin's girlfriend.

607
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:46,564
What other title is there?

608
00:37:52,470 --> 00:37:53,704
I thought you got scared and ran away.

609
00:37:56,007 --> 00:37:57,308
Why did you call so many people?

610
00:37:59,477 --> 00:38:00,144
I thought

611
00:38:01,746 --> 00:38:03,748
there is strength in numbers.

612
00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:05,650
It's also lively.

613
00:38:07,551 --> 00:38:08,786
Most importantly, with more people,

614
00:38:10,187 --> 00:38:11,289
they are all witnesses.

615
00:38:12,189 --> 00:38:13,124
It won't be easy for you to go back on it.

616
00:38:15,026 --> 00:38:16,160
This isn't ring toss.

617
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:16,827
It's a trap.

618
00:38:19,196 --> 00:38:19,563
Exactly.

619
00:38:21,399 --> 00:38:22,633
To trap both of us.

620
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:29,073
I know

621
00:38:31,676 --> 00:38:32,877
I still have many shortcomings.

622
00:38:34,078 --> 00:38:34,712
As a person,

623
00:38:35,413 --> 00:38:36,147
I'm annoying,

624
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:37,682
selfish,

625
00:38:38,549 --> 00:38:39,317
stubborn,

626
00:38:42,119 --> 00:38:43,087
I don't know how to consider others,

627
00:38:44,689 --> 00:38:45,990
and everything revolves around me.

628
00:38:47,425 --> 00:38:48,392
I do things without considering the consequences.

629
00:38:50,094 --> 00:38:50,528
But I believe

630
00:38:50,561 --> 00:38:51,562
I love you more

631
00:38:51,562 --> 00:38:52,329
than anyone else in the world.

632
00:39:04,375 --> 00:39:05,409
If you like hearing it,

633
00:39:06,077 --> 00:39:06,944
I can keep saying it.

634
00:39:08,846 --> 00:39:10,247
But it may take some time.

635
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:13,317
It will take a lifetime.

636
00:39:20,191 --> 00:39:20,958
Are you willing to listen?

637
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:35,806
Still playing?

638
00:39:37,675 --> 00:39:38,442
One last chance.

639
00:39:45,449 --> 00:39:45,950
Where are you going?

640
00:39:47,485 --> 00:39:48,152
To throw the sandbag.

641
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:52,723
The target is right here.

642
00:40:04,335 --> 00:40:05,269
This time, there is only yes,

643
00:40:05,803 --> 00:40:06,437
no no.

644
00:40:12,009 --> 00:40:12,476
Congratulations.

645
00:40:12,510 --> 00:40:13,477
You won the ultimate prize.

646
00:40:14,512 --> 00:40:15,346
No taking back your move.

647
00:40:30,728 --> 00:40:31,328
Fang Xiaoran.

648
00:40:33,230 --> 00:40:33,964
Let's get married.

649
00:40:36,867 --> 00:40:37,968
Let us become family.

650
00:41:19,877 --> 00:41:20,711
It's too big.

651
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,114
I measured it with my pinky.

652
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:25,249
How is it this much too big?

653
00:41:26,183 --> 00:41:26,784
Then

654
00:41:27,451 --> 00:41:28,285
leave some room

655
00:41:28,953 --> 00:41:29,854
for the future.

656
00:41:31,589 --> 00:41:32,289
Stop filming me.

657
00:41:32,356 --> 00:41:33,490
Saying yes once is enough.

658
00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:47,771
What is so urgent?

659
00:41:48,105 --> 00:41:49,306
I have good news for you.

660
00:41:49,974 --> 00:41:50,708
What good news?

661
00:41:51,375 --> 00:41:53,010
Our paper has been accepted.

662
00:41:53,444 --> 00:41:54,011
Really?

663
00:41:59,917 --> 00:42:00,451
That's wonderful.

664
00:42:00,951 --> 00:42:01,652
Academic recognition.

665
00:42:01,752 --> 00:42:02,786
The study on nanoparticle delivery

666
00:42:02,953 --> 00:42:03,554
reversing cardiomyopathy

667
00:42:03,587 --> 00:42:04,488
in primates.

668
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:06,523
That means

669
00:42:06,757 --> 00:42:08,158
we are one step closer

670
00:42:08,292 --> 00:42:09,293
to human clinical trials.

671
00:42:11,495 --> 00:42:12,129
That's amazing.

672
00:42:12,429 --> 00:42:13,931
You got accepted even without my help.

673
00:42:13,998 --> 00:42:14,732
How lucky.

674
00:42:16,033 --> 00:42:17,401
That wasn't luck.

675
00:42:17,668 --> 00:42:18,869
It was strength.

676
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:20,104
Yes, strength. Strength.

677
00:42:20,304 --> 00:42:21,005
Everyone is off work, right?

678
00:42:21,171 --> 00:42:22,072
Let's go celebrate.

679
00:42:22,239 --> 00:42:22,573
Okay.

680
00:42:25,009 --> 00:42:25,442
Sounds good.
